en_649290_0	The Sri Lanka Information Technology Association says that there is a tendency for social media websites to exchange slanderous / fake news and hate statements based on presidential elections to affect the privacy and rights of others.
en_649290_1	The Association states that this has been revealed by the studies carried out by its association.
en_649290_2	The Association points out that such content is posted on social media websites using fake social media accounts.
en_649290_3	Creating fake accounts, publishing fake news and hate statements is contrary to the community guidelines of social media websites.
en_649290_4	The Sri Lanka Information Technology Society further stated that the social media website has provided users with the facility of removing such fake accounts from their social media sites.
en_649290_5	The Association calls on the public to report if they come across any hate or fake news on social media.
